Installation
============

1. Install Fabric v. 1.4.0
    `sudo easy_install fabric==1.4.0`

2. Clone repo
    `git clone <url>`

3. Deploy
    `VIRTUAL_ENV="/wherever/you/want/virtualenv/to/be/installed/" fab activate:local deploy`


Running backend tests
=====================

  To run functional tests, while in virtualenv, run

    $ trial lyrics.grabbers.functional_tests


Running frontend tests
======================

1. Install js test driver

    $ brew install js-test-driver

2. Start JSTD server

    $ js-test-driver --port 9876

3. In target browsers, open [http://localhost:9876]

4. Compile CoffeScript tests to JavaScript

    $ coffee --compile --output static/js/tests/compiled static/js/tests/*.coffee

5. From projects root folder, containing `jsTestDriver.conf`, run

    $ js-test-driver --reset --tests all
